📌 Purpose:
Used to read data from a .properties file (Configuration File).

Example:
config.properties
-----------------
url=https://www.google.com
browser=chrome

----------------------------------------------------

1. Get Project Root Path
------------------------
String projectRootPath = System.getProperty("user.dir");

✔ Returns current project directory path.
✔ Avoids hardcoding file paths.

Example Output:
C:\Users\Sameer\IdeaProjects\MyProject

----------------------------------------------------

2. Create Properties Object
---------------------------
Properties properties = new Properties();

✔ Properties class is used to read key-value pairs.
✔ Available in java.util.Properties package.

----------------------------------------------------

3. Open Properties File
-----------------------
FileInputStream fis =
new FileInputStream(projectRootPath +
"//resource//config.propertiesFile1");

✔ FileInputStream opens the file for reading.
✔ Throws FileNotFoundException if file doesn't exist.

----------------------------------------------------

4. Load Data into Properties Object
-----------------------------------
properties.load(fis);

✔ Reads all key-value pairs from the file.
✔ Stores them in memory.

Example:
url=https://google.com
browser=chrome

----------------------------------------------------

5. Read Value using Key
-----------------------
properties.getProperty("url");

✔ Returns value associated with the key.

Example:
url=https://google.com

Output:
https://google.com

----------------------------------------------------

6. Print Value
--------------
System.out.println(properties.getProperty("url"));

✔ Prints the URL value from properties file.

----------------------------------------------------

Exceptions
----------
IOException
    ├── FileNotFoundException
    └── Other File Reading Errors

Current Code:
public static void main(String[] args) throws IOException

✔ Handles all file-related exceptions.

----------------------------------------------------

Flow of Execution
-----------------
Step 1 -> Get Project Path
Step 2 -> Create Properties Object
Step 3 -> Open Properties File using FileInputStream
Step 4 -> Load File Data
Step 5 -> Read Property Value using Key
Step 6 -> Print Value

----------------------------------------------------

Interview Questions
-------------------

Q1. Why use Properties File?
Ans:
To store configuration data separately from code.
Examples:
- URL
- Browser
- Username
- Password
- Environment Details

Q2. Why use System.getProperty("user.dir")?
Ans:
To get project root directory dynamically instead of hardcoding paths.

Q3. What does properties.load() do?
Ans:
Loads key-value pairs from a properties file into memory.

Q4. Difference between getProperty() and setProperty()?
Ans:
getProperty() → Reads value
setProperty() → Adds/Updates value

Q5. Which package contains Properties class?
Ans:
java.util.Properties

----------------------------------------------------

One-Line Summary:
Properties File = Store Config Data ➜ FileInputStream Opens File ➜
Properties.load() Reads Data ➜ getProperty() Retrieves Value.